subject: Conflict with PowerToys run keyboard shortcut
problem_text: Área: PowerToys Run. Problema: Conflict with PowerToys run keyboard shortcut. Comportamiento: _No response_. Pasos para reproducir: The shortcut for powertoys run (alt + space) conflicts with copilot shortcut !!!
answer:
You are always free to change the keyboard shortcuts to whatever you want. You'll find there are lots of apps with keyboard shortcuts which conflict with one another. It's impossible for everyone to pick unique values. 

That's why it's always important to give users settings to control things like this.
steps_to_reproduce: The shortcut for powertoys run (alt + space) conflicts with copilot shortcut !!!
expected_behavior: change the default keys for both applications.

subject: Command Palette auto starts when disabled
problem_text: Área: Command Palette. Problema: Command Palette auto starts when disabled. Comportamiento: Auto-starts with Windows.. Pasos para reproducir: Disable Command Palette under the dashboard and then restart the computer. Command palette auto-starts even though it's disabled. To get it to go away, toggle the switch in the dashboard, and it closes.
answer:
PowerToys is still set to start on login, right? 

In 0.1 we decided that since CmdPal is just a part of PowerToys, we'll just use PT's startup task, rather than our own. 

You should be able to disable the CmdPal module within PT's settings, and that should prevent it from launching when PowerToys does.
steps_to_reproduce: Disable Command Palette under the dashboard and then restart the computer. Command palette auto-starts even though it's disabled. To get it to go away, toggle the switch in the dashboard, and it closes.
expected_behavior: Command Palette doesn't launch since it's disabled

subject: COMException: DwmExtendFrameIntoClientArea crashes PowerToys Run and causes screen flicker
problem_text:
Área: FancyZones, PowerToys Run. Problema: COMException: DwmExtendFrameIntoClientArea crashes PowerToys Run and causes screen flicker. Comportamiento: PowerToys Run triggers a COMException related to DWM (DwmExtendFrameIntoClientArea), causing the screen to flicker/turn off briefly, and then displays an error dialog.. Pasos para reproducir: 1. Launch Windows and PowerToys starts automatically.
2. Use PowerToys Run (`Alt + Space`) to open it.
3. PowerToys Run fails to render properly.
4. Screen flashes (goes black briefly), then returns.
5. PowerToys shows an error window with COMException.
steps_to_reproduce:
1. Launch Windows and PowerToys starts automatically.
2. Use PowerToys Run (`Alt + Space`) to open it.
3. PowerToys Run fails to render properly.
4. Screen flashes (goes black briefly), then returns.
5. PowerToys shows an error window with COMException.
expected_behavior: PowerToys Run opens with no visual glitches or screen flickering, and displays its interface properly.
actual_behavior: PowerToys Run triggers a COMException related to DWM (DwmExtendFrameIntoClientArea), causing the screen to flicker/turn off briefly, and then displays an error dialog.

subject: Changing hotkeys to WIN+Space does not work for Windows Command Palette
problem_text:
Área: Command Palette. Problema: Changing hotkeys to WIN+Space does not work for Windows Command Palette. Comportamiento: Nothing happens.. Pasos para reproducir: 1. Change hotkey to WIN+Space.
2. Attempt to use that hotkey.
answer: Did you enable the "low-level keyboard hook" or not?
steps_to_reproduce:
1. Change hotkey to WIN+Space.
2. Attempt to use that hotkey.
expected_behavior: The Command Palette to appear when the hotkeys are hit.

subject: Hosts File Editor causes hosts entries to fail when comments include Japanese text
problem_text:
Área: Hosts File Editor. Problema: Hosts File Editor causes hosts entries to fail when comments include Japanese text. Comportamiento: Ping fails with:
Ping request could not find host example.test. Please check the name and try again.

Removing the Japanese comment allows the entry to work as expected:
127.0.0.1 example.test. Pasos para reproducir: 1. Open PowerToys → Hosts File Editor
2. Add the following entry:
127.0.0.1 example.test # Japanese comment（日本語でのコメント）
3. Save and close Hosts File Editor
4. Open Command Prompt and run:
ping example.test
answer: Fixed in 0.71 release of PowerToys. [aka.ms/installpowertoys](https://aka.ms/installpowertoys)
steps_to_reproduce:
1. Open PowerToys → Hosts File Editor
2. Add the following entry:
127.0.0.1 example.test # Japanese comment（日本語でのコメント）
3. Save and close Hosts File Editor
4. Open Command Prompt and run:
ping example.test
expected_behavior: example.test should resolve to 127.0.0.1 as defined in the hosts file.
actual_behavior:
Ping fails with:
Ping request could not find host example.test. Please check the name and try again.

Removing the Japanese comment allows the entry to work as expected:
127.0.0.1 example.test
additional_info:
- OS: Windows 11 Pro 22H2
- System Language: Japanese
- Hosts file encoding: ANSI
- Edited via: PowerToys Hosts File Editor
- Verified using: Command Prompt (ping), browser

Note:
The issue appears to stem from the use of non-ASCII (Japanese) characters in inline comments, which causes the OS to ignore the entire line.

subject: Taskbar icon not visible in light mode
problem_text:

**light** on light gray when in **Light** mode
and
**dark** on Dark gray in **Dark** mode.. Pasos para reproducir: 1. Open Windows **Settings** > **Personalization** > **Colors**.
2. Set the theme to **Light**.
3. Launch powertoys settings or any other window.
4. Look at the taskbar buttons (Minimize, maximize, close) - White on light Gray
answer: yeah, since you weren't the one who opened the issue the bot doesn't pick up your feedback to keep the issue alive.
steps_to_reproduce:
1. Open Windows **Settings** > **Personalization** > **Colors**.
2. Set the theme to **Light**.
3. Launch powertoys settings or any other window.
4. Look at the taskbar buttons (Minimize, maximize, close) - White on light Gray
expected_behavior:
The icons should be **dark** on light gray when in **Light** mode
and
**light** on Dark gray in **Dark** mode.

**light** on light gray when in **Light** mode
and

subject: [Command Palette] Customized shortcuts don't work
problem_text:
Área: Command Palette. Problema: [Command Palette] Customized shortcuts don't work. Comportamiento: Command Palette only respond when associate with the default shortcut. Pasos para reproducir: * use the default shortcut
* Command Palette is launched
* open Command Palette settings
* change shortcut to whatever you want (in my case, I use "Win+Space", but I also tried "Win+Ctrl+Space")
* use the shortcut
* nothing happen
* use the default shortcut
* nothing happen
* revert the shortcut to default
* use the shortcut
* Command Palette is launched

[PowerToysReport_2025-05-26-10-16-21.zip](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/20437944/PowerToysReport_2025-05-26-10-16-21.zip)
answer: Yea this definitely sounds like you didn't enable the low-level keyboard hook. Can you try enabling that and try again?
steps_to_reproduce:
* use the default shortcut
* Command Palette is launched
* open Command Palette settings
* change shortcut to whatever you want (in my case, I use "Win+Space", but I also tried "Win+Ctrl+Space")
* use the shortcut
* nothing happen
* use the default shortcut
* nothing happen
* revert the shortcut to default
* use the shortcut
* Command Palette is launched

[PowerToysReport_2025-05-26-10-16-21.zip](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/20437944/PowerToysReport_2025-05-26-10-16-21.zip)
expected_behavior: Command Palette should respond when associated with a customized shortcut
actual_behavior: Command Palette only respond when associate with the default shortcut

subject: Peek - always white background between photos.
problem_text:
Área: Peek. Problema: Peek - always white background between photos.. Comportamiento: _No response_. Pasos para reproducir: Why not make a transition between photos without a white background? Even if with a delay. Eyes get very tired when the white background flashes when switching.
Try to figure out how to make a transition between photos, but definitely not through white.


And additional.. please add save as button, for save a photo.
answer:
Hi @dualjack. Thanks for your feedback, and I'm sorry this is taking some time to resolve. It was waiting behind some other work on Peek which would make the improvement easier to apply for _all_ previewers, not just the image previewer.

However, I have thought for a while that it might just be best to submit the improvements which affect the image previewer first and leave the generic fix for a later date. This will help fix what I suspect is the most problematic instance of the flashing - where someone is quickly previewing files in an image folder.

There are a couple of other changes which I'm working on at the moment, but I'll get to this as soon as I can.

Thanks again.
steps_to_reproduce:
Why not make a transition between photos without a white background? Even if with a delay. Eyes get very tired when the white background flashes when switching.
Try to figure out how to make a transition between photos, but definitely not through white.


And additional.. please add save as button, for save a photo.
